    <p>Our an­swer is al­ways ‘no’.</p>
    <p>MR AN­DREW TJIOE, chief ex­ec­u­tive of TungLok Group, on cus­tomers try­ing to make reser­va­tions for more than five peo­ple .</p>
    <p>As long as we do not min­gle across ta­bles, we are not break­ing any rules, I think? But I un­der­stand that go­ing out as a group big­ger than five makes things dif­fi­cult.</p>
    <p>MS CRYS­TAL LOH, mar­ket­ing in­tern.</p>


